Description
-----------
This patch should make the Amiga classic game Hunter work with the AGA 
chipset and 68020+ processors (040/060 unknown - please tell me!).  A 
side-effect is that the game will run smoother on an A1200 or above
(optimum is an 030 and/or fast memory:)~~~

Usage
-----
The patch should be run before Hunter.  It can be run from a floppy disk or 
harddisk, although Hunter will still be booted from floppy.

Installation
------------
To use from floppy, extract to a blank disk, then make it bootable using 
"Install DF0:" from a Shell, with that disk in the drive.  To use from 
harddisk, you only need HunterFix, HunterFix.exe, and HunterFix.info (the 
icon).  A real icon for Hunter would be appreciated (send me any offers)!

